 other algorithms for fully\nconnected problems of average difficulty with bimodal disorder. The next\ngeneration of the DA is expected to be able to solve fully connected problems\nup to 8192 variables in size. This would enable the study of fundamental\nphysics problems and industrial applications that were previously inaccessible\nusing standard computing hardware or special-purpose quantum annealing\nmachines.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 22 Jun 2018 18:38:41 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 11 Aug 2018 00:21:06 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sun, 7 Apr 2019 23:47:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-04-09"}
