e two-dimensional Hubbard model, the effective\ndensity-density interaction is peaked at a nonzero frequency, so that solving\nthe mean-field equations already involves a functional equation instead of\nsimply a matrix equation (on a technical level, similar to incommensurate\nphases). Within a certain approximation, we show that such an interaction leads\nto a short quasiparticle lifetime.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 23 Jun 2018 09:11:16 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 31 Aug 2019 18:43:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-09-04"}
